## Welcome to your Containerlab

Let's first take a good look at what you're going to be working with:

![Containerlab Overview](Containerlab.svg)

In this diagram, you will be working with three components, called _nodes_ in Containerlab. From
left to right they are:

1.  `vpp1`: A VPP Router that is connected to a shared subnet with other pariticipants, and to a
    second VPP router.
1.  `vpp2`: A VPP router that is connected to `vpp1` and a Linux container
1.  `client`: A Linux node that is connected behind the two VPP routers.

## Goals for this Training

You will work through the configuration of both VPP routers, so that you connect your lab to all the
other labs run by other participants. If you're successful, you will be able to connect to a
webserver running behind another router on the 'Shared LAN'.

You will learn:

*   VPP configuration using `vppcfg`
*   Bird2 configuration of OSPF
*   Bird2 configuration of BGP
*   `traceroute` and `ping` to explore the LAB network
*   `curl` to fetch HTML files from a webserver

