### Step 6: Configuring the Shared LAN on VPP1

![Step 6](Containerlab Step 6.svg)

Your lab is interconnected with every other participant's lab using a shared network. You have been
assigned an IPv4 and IPv6 address in this shared network:

*    IPv4: `192.0.2.{{id}}/24`
*    IPv6: `2001:db8:8298::{{ '%x' % id }}/64`

By now, you've practiced adding addresses to VPP several times, for this you'll edit
`/config/vpp/vppcfg.yaml` and commit it, like so:

```
root@vpp1:/# nano /config/vpp/vppcfg.yaml
interfaces:
  eth1:
    description: 'To vpplab shared LAN'
    mtu: 1500
    lcp: eth1
>>    addresses: [ 192.0.2.{{ id }}/24, 2001:db8:8298::{{ '%x' % id }}/64 ]
...
```

Once you've edited the VPP config file and added the addresses shown in green above, you can check
it and commit it with:

```
root@vpp1:/# vppcfg plan
root@vpp1:/# vppcfg apply
```

If all is well, you should now be able to reach the Teacher's `vpp1` router:

```
root@vpp1:/# ping 192.0.2.254
root@vpp1:/# ping 2001:db8:8298::fe
```

Do both IPv4 and IPv6 address ping? Then you're ready to go to the last configuration step!

