### Step 8: End to End test

![Step 8](Containerlab Step 8.svg)

Your Containerlab is one of the ones on the right here. The Teacher has also deployed a
containerlab, with a webserver in it. You can see it on the bottom left, with the red circle around
it. It has a well known IPv4 and IPv6 address, which are announced by the Teacher's `vpp1` node.

*    IPv4: `10.0.0.66`
*    IPv6: `2001:db8:0:100::2`

Make sure you can ping the reach the server from your lab, by tracerouting it:

```
[*]─[client]─[/]
└──> traceroute 10.0.0.66
traceroute to 10.0.0.66 (10.0.0.66), 30 hops max, 60 byte packets
 1  10.0.{{id}}.65 (10.0.{{id}}.65)  6.811 ms  7.121 ms  6.887 ms
 2  10.0.{{id}}.16 (10.0.{{id}}.16)  18.540 ms  18.440 ms  17.123 ms
 3  192.0.2.254 (192.0.2.254)  30.380 ms  30.112 ms  42.760 ms
 4  10.0.0.17 (10.0.0.17)  48.495 ms  49.110 ms  50.120 ms
 5  10.0.0.66 (10.0.0.66)  50.470 ms  50.465 ms  50.458 ms

[*]─[client]─[/]
└──> traceroute 2001:db8:0:100::2
traceroute to 2001:db8:0:100::2 (2001:db8:0:100::2), 30 hops max, 80 byte packets
 1  2001:db8:{{ '%x' % id }}:100::1 (2001:db8:{{ '%x' % id }}:100::1)  10.717 ms  12.220 ms  17.543 ms
 2  2001:db8:{{ '%x' % id }}:1::1 (2001:db8:{{ '%x' % id }}:1::1)  34.658 ms  37.112 ms  53.117 ms
 3  2001:db8:8298::fe (2001:db8:8298::fe)  42.640 ms  58.228 ms  55.455 ms
 4  2001:db8:0:1::2 (2001:db8:0:1::2)  62.644 ms  72.871 ms  73.550 ms
 5  2001:db8:0:100::2 (2001:db8:0:100::2)  74.615 ms  74.609 ms  74.607 ms
```

You are now ready to complete the training! Using a web client called `curl`, you can fetch a
special three-word token that the server serves specifically to your Containerlab client. These
tokens are unique to each Containerlab. Write them in the table below to complete your training:
  
``` 
[*]─[client]─[/]
└──> curl 10.0.0.66

[*]─[client]─[/]
└──> curl [2001:db8:0:100::2]
```

